telling you that the materiall oyle, wherwith Chriſtians were anoynted, was called by Cyrill the Antitype of Chriſts owne anoynting, which was the Spirit of God it ſelfe. That The eſſentiall Spirit of God is oppoſed to the Antitype, which was materiall oyle. And, notwithſtanding, that the ſame Antitype is called by Cyrill the Spirit of God; and after, that the Chriſtians are ſayd to receive the Spirit;
